This paper presents a method for generating compact Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) by identifying and removing redundant filters from an over-parameterized network. The paper focuses on the efficiency and performance of neural networks, which are topics that fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and data structures (cs.DS). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
